                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <handNote scribe="JonErl001" scope="sole" script="humbook">
                        <p>Written by Jón Erlendsson in a seventeenth century fracture-hand.</p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>In the first part of the manuscript corrections occur. According to <name
                           type="person" key="JonSig004">Jón Sigurðsson</name> (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary-1" target="JSKat">Catalogue of AM 1-239 fol.</ref>
                        </bibl>, <ref>AM 394 fol., fol. 54v</ref>) these are made by bishop <name
                           type="person" key="BrySve001">Brynjólfur Sveinsson</name> and <name
                           type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>. On fol.
                           <locus>1r</locus> in the lower margin <name type="person" key="SveTor001"
                           >Sveinn Torfason</name> stated his ownership: <q>Þeßa sgubok ä eg
                           Vnderskrifadur Sveirn Torfa<lb/>son Anno. 1695</q>. His name is once
                        repeated in the margin.</p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <p>Bound in a pachment cover from <date notBefore="1700" notAfter="1730"
                              >1700-1730</date>; <dimensions type="binding">
                              <height unit="mm">291</height>
                              <width unit="mm">194</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">38</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                           <!--REFERENCE TO PICTURE 234-->
                           <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> wrote the title
                           in black ink on the spine<!--REFERENCE TO PICTURE 235-->.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <accMat>
                     <p>There are four AM-slips (a-d) inserted between the paste down and the first
                        page, although (a) and (d) concern AM 41 fol. Slip (b) reads: <q>Ur bök
                           Sveins Torfasonar.</q>, and slip (c) reads: <q>Sumstad<ex>ar</ex>
                           misskrifad.</q>
                     </p>
                  </accMat>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in <origDate
                           notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699">the seventeenth century</origDate>.</p>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>The manuscript once belonged to <name type="person" key="SveTor001">Sveinn
                           Torfason</name> who also wrote his name and the date <date when="1695"
                           >1695</date> in bottom margin of fol. 1r. <name type="person"
                           key="JonSig004">Jón Sigurðsson</name> (<bibl>
                           <ref type="secondary-1" target="JSKat">Catalogue of AM 1-239 fol.</ref>
                        </bibl>, <ref>AM 394 fol., fol. 54v</ref>) assumes that the previous known
                        owner, bishop <name type="person" key="BrySve001">Brynjólfur
                           Sveinsson</name>, passed the manuscript on to the priest <name
                           type="person" key="TorJon002">Torfi Jónsson</name> of <name type="place"
                           key="GauGau01">Gaulverjabær</name>, who in his turn gave it to his son
                           <name type="person" key="SveTor001">Sveinn</name>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Jón Sigurðsson (ibid.) also assumes that <name type="person" key="ArnMag001"
                           >Árni Magnússon</name> acquired the manuscript from <name type="person"
                           key="SveTor001">Sveinn Torfason</name>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
